   Who's News:
   AM International Inc.
</HL>
<DATE>
04/10/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C25
</SO>
<CO>
   AM WNEWS
</CO>
<LP>
   AM INTERNATIONAL Inc. (Chicago) -- The company said it
merged its AM Multigraphics and international divisions under
the AM Multigraphics title and named George H. Gilmore Jr.
president of the new unit. Mr. Gilmore, 40 years old, headed
the international division and is a former president of Mitel
Inc. The graphics-equipment concern said Gerald J. McConnell,
47, vice president and head of the former AM Multigraphics
unit, resigned from the company to pursue other interests.
</LP>
