<HL>
   Transco Unit Tests Gas Wells
</HL>
<DATE>
04/10/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A16
</SO>
<CO>
   E NBL NES
</CO>
<IN>
PIPELINE OPERATORS (PIP)
</IN>
<LP>
   HOUSTON -- Transco Exploration &amp; Production Co., a unit of
Transco Energy Co., said it tested five natural-gas wells in
the Gulf of Mexico that it expects to have onstream in the
third quarter.
   Four development wells, scheduled for platform
installation this summer, are located 162 miles southeast of
Houston at East Cameron Block 109, Transco said. Transco is
the operator and has a 76% interest in the wells. Zilkha
Energy Co. owns the balance.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The company also said it completed a well at Brazos Block
491. Transco has 38% of that well. Zilkha has 16%; a
subsidiary of Noble Affiliates Inc. has 23%; and a subsidiary
of New England Electric System has 23%.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO>
WSJ900410-0110
</DOCNO>
<DOCID>
900410-0110.
</DOCID>
<HL>
   Metro Airlines
</HL>
<DATE>
04/10/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B7
</SO>
<CO>
   MAIR
</CO>
<IN>
AIRLINES (AIR)
</IN>
<LP>
   DALLAS -- Metro Airlines said March traffic was 50.9
million revenue passenger miles, up 68.4% from March 1989. A
revenue passenger mile is the equivalent of flying one paying
passenger one mile.
   Metro's load factor increased to 53.1%, from 46.8%. For
the quarter, Metro flew 135.8 million revenue passenger
miles, up 48.6% from a year ago. The airline's load factor in
the first three months rose to 50.4%, from 47.6% last year.
</LP>
