   PHOENIX, Ariz. -- America West Airlines said its March
traffic increased 35.5%, to 941.8 million revenue passenger
miles. A revenue passenger mile is the equivalent of flying
one paying passenger one mile.
   America West said its load factor rose to 65.2%, from
62.4% a year earlier. The airline said first-quarter traffic
increased 35.6% over the 1989 period, to 2.5 billion revenue
passenger miles, and its first-quarter load factor rose to
61.9%, from 59.8%.
