<LP>
   FRANKFURT, West Germany -- West Germany's total capital
account deficit narrowed to 5.68 billion marks ($3.35
billion) in February from 9.80 billion marks ($5.78 billion)
in January, the Deutsche Bundesbank said.
   The long-term capital account deficit widened to 19.10
billion marks from 545 million a month earlier, the West
German central bank said.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The short-term capital account swung to a surplus of 13.42
billion marks from a deficit of 9.26 billion in January, the
Bundesbank said.
