<HL>
   OPEC Output Rose in March
</HL>
<DATE>
04/10/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   MDEST
</CO>
<IN>
PETROLEUM (PET)
MONETARY NEWS, FOREIGN EXCHANGE, TRADE (MON)
</IN>
<LP>
   MANAMA, Bahrain -- Crude oil production by the 13-member
Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries totaled
24,090,000 barrels a day in March, up from 23,620,000 barrels
daily in February, according to estimates published by the
Cyprus-based oil industry newsletter Middle East Economic
Survey.
   The newsletter said the March output is marginally higher
than last year's monthly peak of 24 million barrels a day,
recorded in December, and represents the highest monthly OPEC
production since 1981.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   OPEC production averaged 23,660,000 barrels a day during
the first quarter, roughly level with the 23.7 million
barrels a day recorded during the final quarter of 1989, the
newsletter said.
