<DOCNO>
WSJ900410-0069
</DOCNO>
<DOCID>
900410-0069.
</DOCID>
<HL>
   Hong Kong Exports Fall
</HL>
<DATE>
04/10/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C15
</SO>
<CO>
   FREST
</CO>
<IN>
MONETARY NEWS, FOREIGN EXCHANGE, TRADE (MON)
</IN>
<LP>
   HONG KONG -- Hong Kong's total exports contracted 2% in
volume terms in January from a year earlier, pulled down by a
contraction in domestic exports, according to government data
released Monday.
   While re-exports grew 1% in January, exports of items
produced in the colony fell 5%. Meanwhile, imports decreased
7%.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   In value terms, domestic exports rose 2% in January from a
year earlier, while re-exports climbed 5%. The price of
imported goods rose 3%. Actual cash values weren't provided.
</TEXT>
