   PLYMOUTH, Mich. -- Highland Superstores Inc. reported
March sales of $68.2 million, down 2% from sales of $69.6
million a year earlier. Comparable-store sales declined 9%.
   The consumer electronics retailer said its sales for the
first two months of the year were $127.5 million, down 4%
from $133.2 million in the year-earlier period.
Comparable-store sales dropped 11%.
