<HL>
   Business Brief -- Abbott Laboratories:
   Net Rose 14% on Increase
   In Sales in First Quarter
</HL>
<DATE>
04/10/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C14
</SO>
<CO>
   ABT
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
MEDICAL SUPPLIES (MDS)
</IN>
<LP>
   Abbott Laboratories reported a 14% rise in net income for
the first quarter on an 11% sales rise, continuing the recent
solid growth by the North Chicago, Ill., maker of hospital
products and pharmaceuticals.
   Net income was $225 million, or $1.02 a share, up from the
year-earlier period's $198 million, or 88 cents a share.
Sales rose to $1.44 billion from $1.3 billion.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Abbott said the introduction of products with higher
profit margins, as well as productivity increases contributed
to the upturn.
   The company's international sales increased more than
domestic sales, climbing about 12% compared with 10% growth
in the U.S.
   In New York Stock Exchange composite trading yesterday,
Abbott rose 50 cents to $68.125.
</TEXT>
