   Business Brief -- Western Co. of North America:
   Norwegian Firm Buys Stake
   Of 5.9% in Texas Concern
</HL>
<DATE>
04/10/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C18
</SO>
<CO>
   WSN
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Arcade Shipping AS, a Norwegian offshore drilling
investment company, said it acquired a 5.9% stake in Western
Co. of North America, Fort Worth, Texas, and may seek board
representation.
   In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission,
Arcade said it holds 740,000 Western common shares, all
bought between Jan. 4 to March 15 for $13.425 to $17.70 a
share.
