<HL>
   Business Brief -- Transcon Inc.:
   Truck-a-Way Inc. Group
   Has 5.2% Stake in Common
</HL>
<DATE>
04/10/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C15
</SO>
<CO>
   TCL
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   A group including Truck-a-Way Inc., a Vacaville, Calif.,
trucking concern, said it holds a 5.2% stake in Transcon
Inc.'s common shares outstanding.
   In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission,
the group said it holds 329,000 Transcon common shares,
including 266,900 bought from March 22 to March 30 for 93.75
cents to $1.375 a share.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The group said it acquired its Transcon stock for
investment purposes, but that its intentions are "subject to
continual review and re-evaluation."
   Other group members are James D. Burke, president of
Truck-a-Way, and Andrew J. Collins Jr., an officer and
director of Metropolitan Trust Co., a Sherwood, Ark.,
diversified real estate concern.
   In Beverly Hills, Calif., Transcon officials couldn't be
reached to comment on the Truck-a-Way stake. Transcon, a
trucking company, earlier this month said it sold its
Transcon Lines carrier to closely held, Miami-based Growth
Finance Corp. The price wasn't disclosed. It said the unit in
1989 had revenue of $226.5 million and operating losses of
$31.6 million.
